<CAPTION>  Photo; PHOTO: See Bob Hartman and his puppets at the Christmas Crafts Jamboree
next weekend at the Santa Clara Convention Center.  </CAPTION>
<DESCRIPT>  FAMILY; ENTERTAINMENT  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  HOLIDAY fun for the entire family and arts and crafts are combined at the
Santa Clara County Holiday Faire and Christmas Lane Show, open today and
Friday through next Sunday in San Jose.;   Hours are 11 a.m. to 6 p.m. at the
Santa Clara County Fairgrounds, 344 Tully Road, San Jose.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Living  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  'TIS THE PRESEASON FOR CELEBRATING  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  Family Clipboard; Things to do  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     New this year are 42 arts and crafts booths in Christmas Lane and 50-cent
carnival rides. For the kids there will be the Swan Bros. Circus and the Land
of the Sweets marionette show, each giving three shows daily. There also will
be make-and-take projects, face painting, pony rides and Santa in an animated
Santa Land, featuring a 10-foot-tall revolving snowman, an ice-skating bear
and a music-box bear. Pictures with Santa are free with coupons from
participating Longs Drug Stores.;   The Christmas Lane Show will highlight
decorating ideas, cooking demonstrations, decorated Christmas trees, arts and
crafts, a candy-cane boutique and a Holiday Market of 110 booths with gifts to
buy. There also will be a Toy Train Village and an Elves Workshop. Admission
is $4; $2 ages 60 and over and 6 to 16; ages 5 and under are free. A new
family admission ticket is $10 for two adults and up to four children. Parking
(usually $3) is free with a donation of canned food. For details call (408)
295-3050.;   (check) The Ice Capades will spotlight Yogi Bear, the Flintstones
and Scooby-Doo in shows Tuesday through next Sunday at the Oakland Coliseum.
Showtimes are 7:30 p.m. Tuesday through Friday; noon, 4 and 8 p.m. Saturday
and 1 and 5 p.m. next Sunday. Tickets are $9 to $14.75. Two-dollar discounts
for kids (12 and under) are available on selected dates. Call (408) 998-2277,
(510) 762-2277.;   (check) To find that special gift try the Christmas Crafts
Jamboree next weekend. Three hundred people with their arts and crafts will
exhibit handmade items while the bands Way Out West and High Strung perform. A
"High Street Circus" vaudeville team will perform while kids are entertained
by Bob Hartman and his puppets. The event will be held from 10 a.m. to 9 p.m.
Friday, 10 a.m. to 8 p.m. Saturday and 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. next Sunday. The
venue is the Santa Clara Convention Center, 5001 Great America Parkway, Santa
Clara. Admission is $4; $1 ages 6 to 12; ages 5 and under are free. (408)
748-7000.;   Events; The Harvest Festival  is in its final day today in San
Jose. Works by 1,500 artists from across the country will be shown in a
19th-century village atmosphere. Featured entertainers will be Sidesaddle,
Ranka's Revue, Marionettes, Stroller's Corner: B.V. Dobbs, Vaudeville Nouveau
comedy juggling, Guido the Magical Clown, the Barbary Coast Cloggers, bands,
acrobats, comedians and folk dancers. Hours are 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. today at the
San Jose McEnery Convention Center, 150 W. San Carlos St., San Jose. Admission
is $6; $5 ages 60 and over; $3 ages 6 to 12; ages 5 and under are free. (707)
778-6300.;   Santa arrives  at Eastridge Mall at 9 a.m. Friday in an indoor
parade of 1,200 participants. After the parade Santa will greet children at
his 32-foot-high sleigh; pictures of children with him will be available to
buy. The parade is the traditional opener of the holiday shopping season at
Eastridge, located east of Highway 101 on Tully Road and Capitol Expressway,
San Jose. (408) 238-3600.;   Entertainment; A "Winnie-the-Pooh Christmas Tail"
 is being performed by the Alameda Children's Musical Theater at 7:30 p.m.
Fridays and 1 and 3 p.m. Saturdays through Dec. 21. The play is being given at
the Children's Music Theater's temporary location, 1912 Central Ave., Alameda.
Admission is $7 adults, $5 seniors and teens, $4 children 12 and under. Bring
a can of food to donate and get $1 off the admission price. (510) 521-6965.;  
"Annie"  has its last performance at 2 p.m. today as the season's opening
presentation by the San Jose Children's Musical Theater. More than 120 young
performers, ages 6 through 20, adult alumni and professionals are in the cast.
The show is performed at the Civic Auditorium, 145 W. San Carlos St., San
Jose. Tickets, all reserved, are $9 to $10. (408) 288-5437 or (408) 246-1160.;
  A children's concert  to the theme of "Around the World in 80 Minutes" will
be held at 3 p.m. today at the Amador Theater, 1155 Santa Rita Road,
Pleasanton. Presented by the Pleasanton Community Concert Band, the concert is
free of charge.;   Exhibits; The Children's Discovery Museum  will be open the
day after Thanksgiving from 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. -- a good opportunity to take
family or holiday visitors. Regular museum hours are 10 a.m. to 5 p.m.
Tuesdays through Saturdays and noon to 5 p.m. Sundays. A Native American
Exploration program will be held at 10:30 a.m. Tuesday and a program of song
and dance across the Americas will be performed at 1 p.m. Saturday. The museum
features interactive exhibits and programs. It is located at Woz Way and
Auzerais Street, San Jose. Admission is $6 adults; $3 ages 4 to 18; ages 3 and
under are free. (408) 298-5437.;   Upcoming; Holiday in the making.  The
creating of ornaments for the birds -- holiday ornaments made out of birdseed.
2 to 4 p.m. Dec. 22, Bay Area Discovery Museum, 557 E. Fort Baker, Sausalito.
$7 plus $3 materials fee. Pre-registration is required; call (415) 332-9646.; 
 ODC/San Francisco Presents  "The Velveteen Rabbit" Friday, Saturday and next
Sunday and Dec. 5 through 8 at the San Francisco Palace of Fine Arts. An East
Bay performance schedule will run Dec. 27-29 at the Walnut Creek Regional
Center for the Arts. San Francisco performances are $16, $12 children; East
Bay performances are $20, $15 children. For times and reservations in San
Francisco, call (415) 392-4400 or (510) 762-2277; for the Walnut Creek show,
call (510) 943-7469, (510) 762-2277.;   San Jose Cleveland Ballet  performs
the holiday classic "The Nutcracker," Dec. 4-8, Center for the Performing
Arts, San Jose. Family performances are 7:30 p.m. Dec. 4 and Dec. 5, 8 p.m.
Dec. 6, 2 and 8 p.m. Dec. 7 and 1:30 and 7:30 p.m. Dec. 8. Special
"Nutcracker" parties will be held before matinees on Saturday and Sunday,
featuring storytelling, coloring, musical entertainment and the "Nutcracker
Prince." Performances $12 to $40; parties $5. (408) 998-2277, (510) 762-2277.  </TEXT>
